Mauritius’s ENL Investment Buys 5.2% of Shares in Rogers

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-08-25T12:57:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/mauritius-s-enl-investment-says-buys-5-2-of-shares-in-rogers.html
ENL Investment Ltd. (ENIT) , a Mauritius
investment company, boosted its stake in Rogers & Co. after
buying 5.2 percent of its traded shares, said Virginie
Corneillet, head of legal and corporate affairs of ENL Group.  The company bought 1.31 million shares in Rogers & Co. on
Aug. 23, Corneillet said by phone today from  Port Louis , the
capital. The purchase increases ENL Investment’s direct, and
indirect stake through a holding company, in Rogers to 31.7
percent, she said.  ENL Investment was unchanged at 36 rupees by the 2:30 p.m.
close in Port Louis.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis at 
